                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-186-victim1390 t18310630-186-viclabel993"></join>. I let the prisoner a room in Snow's-rents, in the month of May, about one week before he was apprehended - I let him the room at 3s. 9d. a week furnished; a neighbour came and told me the prisoner had been seen going out with a large bundle - I went to the room, and missed a pair of sheets, a rug, and a pair of flat irons; he had a wife, as I thought, with him when he took the lodging, and she was there when I missed the things.</p>
